*********************operator overloadig*********************
	* compile time polymorphism
	
List of operator which cann't be overloaded
	1. sizeof
	2. ternary 
	3. pointer to member
	4. scope resolution
	5. typedef
	
types of operator overloading:
	1. unary operator overloading:
	2. binary operator overloading:

With the help of member function and friend function we can overload the operator .

SYNTAX:
	return_type operator_keyword symbol(argument){
		//block of code
	}

example:
	void operator -(){
		--a;
	}
	
calling in main function:
	symbol name_of_object

#include<iostream>
using namespace std;

class abc{
	int m,n;
	public:
		abc(){
			m=5;
			n=8;
		}
		 void show(){
		 	cout<<m<<", "<<n<<endl;
		 }
		 
		 void operator -(){
		 	m*=5;
		 	n*=5;
		 }
		 
};

int main(){
	abc obj;
	obj.show();
	-obj;
	obj.show();
	return 0;
}
